## AUP-001 — Acceptable Use Policy

**SOC 2 Mapping:** CC6.1 — Logical Access Security
**Purpose:** Define acceptable use of company-owned technology assets and data

**Key Policy Statements:**
- All company-owned devices must be used primarily for business purposes
- Personal use is permitted within reasonable limits and must not interfere with business operations
- Employees must not install unauthorized software or access unauthorized systems
- Company data must not be stored on personal devices or unauthorized cloud services
- All use of company assets is subject to monitoring

**Prohibited Activities include:**
- Accessing, downloading, or distributing illegal content
- Sharing login credentials with any other person
- Using company systems to conduct personal business or side activities
- Bypassing security controls or attempting to access unauthorized systems
- Connecting personal devices to the internal network without IT approval

